title: 109_hr2676
content: CERTAIN CHEMICALS AND CHEMICAL MIXTURES are amended in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States by inserting a new heading in numerical sequence. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended to include new headings for certain chemicals and chemical mixtures. Thiamethoxam and mixtures of cis and trans chemicals are listed with specific details and effective dates. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States is amended to include new headings for chemicals and mixtures. Propiconazole, 3-iodo-2-propynyl butylcarbamate, and application adjuvants are listed under specific headings. Mixtures of Pyrimethanil are also included with no changes in classification. The Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States includes new headings for chemicals and mixtures such as propiconazole, 3-iodo-2-propynyl butylcarbamate, and application adjuvants like Philabuster 400SC. Mixtures of Pyrimethanil are also listed with no changes in classification. The curr_chunk provides information on specific chemical compounds, including 1,2-benzisoxazol-3-yl)-1-piperidinyl]ethyl and 3-Benzo[b]thien-2-yl-5,6-dihydro-1,4,2-oxathiazine 4-oxide. These compounds are classified under different subheadings in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. The curr_chunk provides details on specific chemical compounds, such as Chlorfenapyr and 2-(p-Chlorophenyl)-3-cyano-4-bromo-5-. These compounds are classified under different subheadings in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. The curr_chunk discusses the classification of cyano-4-bromo-5-trifluoromethylpyrrole (Econea 028) and mixtures of Pyrimethanil in the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. The amendment made by subsection (a) applies to goods entered on or after the 15th day after the date of the enactment of this Act.
